reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Great product, bad price
reviews.reviewText: I’ve been buying these razors for years and they’ve always been 8$/9$ for 8 refills. Now they’re 30$. Price gouging. BIC also sells this same razor with 7 refills for less than 15$.Why 30$ here? What’s going on?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I will NEVER buy a BIC product EVER again. I bought one package and after 1 month the handle broke. Contacted Amazon and received another package free of charge. After 1 month, broken again in exact same spot. Now I have 20 refill cartridges and NO handle. I’m so disappointed I don’t know what to do. I wish I could give -25 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars The best time to dispose of this disposable razor is before you use it.
reviews.reviewText: If you're okay with just a few shaves on a blade and using a styptic pencil each time for the nicks, this may be for you. Also pricey compared to other blades. I know it's a BIC, but it's not sensible.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars I hate this razor
reviews.reviewText: I bought this razor because the blades for my normal razor were missing, and I was tired of mail order blades. My old razor worked fine, just everyone in the house uses the same brand and steals my blades. Thought I would try this Bic. (I actually thought I ordered Gillette- I screwed up)The handle is comfortable, but the cartridge eject button is right in the middle so you will accidentally hit it all the time. That isn’t my complaint. The blades are junk. They lose their sharpness after 2 shaves, from then on it feels like you are scraping knives across your face. It feels worse than a dry shave. I shave in the shower, the blade clogs with hair and is impossible to clear, even with the massage head, if you tap the head on the shower wall, the blade pops off and is impossible to put back on, soooo you slide out another new blade and get 10 more strokes and feel like it’s dragging broken glass across your face again. I rinse between every other stroke, waste of time. I haven’t had shaver burn in decades, but I’ve had it so bad with these blades I wasn’t able to shave for several days after each try. I tried shaving at the sink ( American Crew moisturizing shave cream) and still my face feels like fire afterward. The trim edge “doesn’t “, it is sharp and cuts hair but not wear you think it is going to cut. Trimming around your nose will make you bleed. And don’t make the mistake of rinse razor and lying flat on the counter- the strips on the razor face will stick to the counter. I threw away the last two blades- I surrender, in a quest for something better. I think I will read comments before buying the next one. If I could give it a minus grade- I would, and I rarely bitch about products. The handle is comfortable, that is the only saving grace- EXCEPT it is too wide to hang in the shaver hanger on the shower mirror- I forgot about that, I had to buy a special shower rack just for that razor 😡

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars You get wat you pay for - when will I learn :(
reviews.reviewText: I've been happy with Gillette for decades, shaving every day, but it seems that their prices, like so many items these days, are darn expensive. On the surface, this Bic seemed just about the same and what could go wrong with TITANTIUM blades. On the 3rd shave I noticed a less than smooth shave. On the 4th shave I got nicked twice - and that never happens with a Gillette. The Bic blades - at least for me - less only 3 days as oppose to almost a month with the Gillette Fusion 5. Twice the cost but 8-9 times the use - seems like simple math to me. YOU GET WHAT YOU PAY FOR. It's about time I learn, but I've been taken plenty :( Bob

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Saw your money
reviews.reviewText: I have been using the hybrid flex 5 for many years.I knew it was to good to be trueThe first blade I used hurt as if it was dull. I figured no biggie and didn’t really think about it. Then the next blade was very discomforting as well.In my opinion the blades are dull , I don’t know how or why , but they are not working as I anticipated. Never had this problem when I purchased them in a store.I suspect moisture somehow got to them and they are very disappointing.Not sure who or what is the blame, but I certainly will only purchase them in a store from now on.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Handle not included.
reviews.reviewText: I had a pack of disposable hybrid 5 razors which gave an excellent shave and lasted much longer than the usual disposable razor. I ordered this because it showed a handle and 8 refills.NO HANDLE INCLUDED!The disposable handle won't release the attached blade (hence the disposable tag) so I have 8 blades that are currently of no use to me. The vendor said they have given me a full refund, I'll check that next.Delivery time was very slow as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars I hope my review can discourage at least one person from buying these razors
reviews.reviewText: I rarely review a low cost everyday item like this, but I felt the need to let other buyers know about the frustrating aspects this product presents. 1) The least amount of hair will clog the razor and it is very difficult to remove. 2) In using this razor, you may make the mistake of bumping it or dropping it. If you do, the razor cartridge will pop off the handle. EVERY TIME. And you will be left to fish for it in the bottom of the shower. 3) The release button for the razor cartridge is HUGE and easy to accidentally touch while using the razor to shave. This causes, you guessed it, the razor to detach from the handle with the slightest touch.Do yourself a favor and just buy a different razor. Your future self will thank you.
